The defendant Jeremy J. Landgraf was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jeremy J. Landgraf is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jeremy J. Landgraf was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

MARQUETTE COUNTY DNA PROOF OF SUBMISSION

Defendant Jeremy J. Landgraf in court with attorney James D. Peebles.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CM130 & 15CM132 tracking:
Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1 in 15CM130 and Ct. 1 in 15CM132.  All other counts in both cases to be dismissed.
Atty Peebles agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest pleas to both cases.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.    Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1 in 15CM130 and Ct. 1 in 15CM132.  All other counts in both cases to be dismissed.

  State has complied with victim notification requirements.
Atty Peebles makes arguments and asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.

BY THE COURT:  15CM130, Ct. 1:  Court orders 60 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber; consecutive to any other sentence
  Report on or before March 31, 2016 by 7:00pm, clean & sober.
Credit = 2 days
Court Costs = $243.00 + $100.00 Domestic Abuse Surcharge
DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
Counts 2, 3 & 4 to be dismissed.
Bond to be applied to all costs; balance to be applied to both cases 15CM130 & 15CM132.  If any balance it is to be returned to the party that posted it.

15CM132, Ct. 1:  Court orders 30 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber; consecutive to any other sentence including 15CM130 sentence
  Report on or before March 31, 2016 by 7:00pm, clean & sober.
Court Costs = $243.00 + $100.00 Domestic Abuse Surcharge
DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
Count 2 to be dismissed.
Bond to be applied

Defendant Jeremy J. Landgraf in court with attorney James D. Peebles.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CM130 & 15CM132 tracking:
 Atty Peebles states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint's in both matters & waives it's reading.  Court finds probable cause in both cases.  Atty Peebles enters a Not Guilty plea in both matters.

BY THE COURT:  Not Guilty plea entered in both cases.
Set for Return.
bond continued in both matters.  Return date scheduled for December 3, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
